TITLE: Finding a Note by ID with Intercom API in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to fetch the details of a single note using the Intercom Node client. It requires the `note_id` to be a valid id of the note within the intercom system. The `client` object is assumed to be initialized with valid API credentials.
SOURCE: https://github.com/intercom/intercom-node/blob/master/reference.md#_snippet_43

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
await client.notes.find({
    note_id: "1",
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Creating a Contact with Intercom API in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a new contact (user or lead) in your Intercom workspace using the Intercom Node client. It requires the `client` object to be initialized and uses the `create` method with an email parameter to create a new contact.  It assumes the Intercom client has been properly initialized.
SOURCE: https://github.com/intercom/intercom-node/blob/master/reference.md#_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
await client.contacts.create({
    email: "joebloggs@intercom.io",
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Listing Conversations using Intercom Conversations API
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to fetch a list of all conversations using the Intercom Conversations API. It shows two ways to iterate through the conversations: using a `for await` loop and manually iterating page by page. Pagination is used to handle large numbers of conversations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/intercom/intercom-node/blob/master/reference.md#_snippet_54

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const response = await client.conversations.list();
for await (const item of response) {
    console.log(item);
}

// Or you can manually iterate page-by-page
const page = await client.conversations.list();
while (page.hasNextPage()) {
    page = page.getNextPage();
}
```

