TITLE: Searching Conversations Using Intercom Node SDK - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet searches Intercom conversations matching custom criteria using the SDK's 'conversations.search' method. It demonstrates constructing a query with operators, filtering by creation timestamp, applying pagination, and handling streaming iteration or manual paging. Dependencies include the Intercom Node SDK and required authentication. Key parameters: the 'query' object (with fields: operator, value, field, operator, value) and 'pagination' (per_page). Returns an async iterator or paginated result containing matching conversation objects. Input types and valid operators depend on the field types; see the operator reference table for constraints.
SOURCE: https://github.com/intercom/intercom-node/blob/master/reference.md#_snippet_58

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
const response = await client.conversations.search({
    query: {
        operator: "AND",
        value: [
            {
                field: "created_at",
                operator: ">",
                value: "1306054154",
            },
        ],
    },
    pagination: {
        per_page: 5,
    },
});
for await (const item of response) {
    console.log(item);
}

// Or you can manually iterate page-by-page
const page = await client.conversations.search({
    query: {
        operator: "AND",
        value: [
            {
                field: "created_at",
                operator: ">",
                value: "1306054154",
            },
        ],
    },
    pagination: {
        per_page: 5,
    },
});
while (page.hasNextPage()) {
    page = page.getNextPage();
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Creating a Data Export Job with Intercom Node Client in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Initiates an asynchronous export job via the Intercom Node.js client, posting to the dataExport resource. Requires specifying at least created_at_after and created_at_before (Unix timestamps) as the date range for export; the timeframe is inclusive. Only one active export job per workspace is allowed. If a job is already pending, the API returns a 429 status. The export job does not include records updated in the range, only those created in the specified window.
SOURCE: https://github.com/intercom/intercom-node/blob/master/reference.md#_snippet_73

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
await client.dataExport.create({
    created_at_after: 1719474967,
    created_at_before: 1719492967,
});
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Updating Contact in Intercom with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to update an existing contact (user or lead) by providing contact_id and the fields to be updated such as email and name.
SOURCE: https://github.com/intercom/intercom-node/blob/master/reference.md#_snippet_32

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
await client.contacts.update({
    contact_id: "63a07ddf05a32042dffac965",
    email: "joebloggs@intercom.io",
    name: "joe bloggs",
});
```

