TITLE: Implementing Pagination for List Endpoints
DESCRIPTION: Shows two methods for handling pagination: using async iterators to loop through all items, or manually iterating page-by-page.
SOURCE: https://github.com/intercom/intercom-node/blob/master/README.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { IntercomClient } from "intercom-client";

const client = new IntercomClient({ token: "YOUR_TOKEN" });
const response = await client.articles.list();
for await (const item of response) {
    console.log(item);
}

// Or you can manually iterate page-by-page
const page = await client.articles.list();
while (page.hasNextPage()) {
